Before getting into Matthew chapter 5, let's do a quick recap of where we're coming from in chapter 4

In verses 1-11, Matthew outlines Jesus' victory over satan as he fasts for 40 days in the wilderness and resists multiple temptations 

Verses 12-17 mark the beginning of Jesus' ministry where be begins preaching publicly, repeating John the baptists urgent message to repent for the kingdom of heaven is near

In verses 18-22 We learn about the recruitment of Jesus' first 4 disciples. 2 pairs of brothers who are fishermen in Galilee: Peter and Andrew, James and John

and in verses 23-25 we read about Jesus preaching the word of God and healing all kinds of diseases and afflictions

Word of Jesus is now spreading and begins drawing massive crowds of people who are coming to hear Jesus' teachings and witness his miracles


That now brings us to chapter 5 which is perhaps the most famous and significant sermon given by Jesus known as sermon on the mount where he shares the beatitudes

I'm going to walk through each of the Beatitudes one at a time because while they are simple and short, they hold profound meaning so I want to unpack them individually

